other_tests.findings: Hepatic echotexture within normal limits. Echogenic lesion in liver segment V measuring 1.1 x 1.1 x 0.8 cm consistent with hemangioma. No intra-or extra-hepatic biliary ductal dilation. Common hepatic duct measures 2 mm. Patent portal vein with appropriate flow. Pancreas and gallbladder appear within normal limits. Right kidney measures 10.7 cm, left kidney measures 11.6 cm; no stones or hydronephrosis identified. Spleen measures 9.6 cm. No ascites. Blind-ending tubular structure representing the appendix with echogenic indurated fat around its tip. Two shadowing appendicoliths in appendiceal lumen with no evidence of abscess.
